<HEAD>REPUBLICANS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 Method: Primary Date: Tuesday, May 3 Presidential filing deadline: Friday, March 4, 1988 Delegates: 51 Delegates allocated: Tuesday, May 3 and Thursday, June 9 Selection of delegates: Wednesday, June 8 and Thursday, June 9 <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> Republicans allocate their national convention delegates at the primary election on May 3 and at the state convention on June 9. Three delegates from each of the state's 10 congressional districts will be awarded to presidential candidates on a winner-take-all basis in each district. The remaining 21 national convention delegates will be chosen at large by the state convention. Their allocation will not be governed by results of the primary.
