<TEXT>
 A Christian Science couple pleaded innocent to manslaughter in the death of their 2 -LCB- - year-old son who died after they refused to seek medical help for him because of their beliefs <PERSON> David </PERSON> and <PERSON> Ginger </PERSON> <PERSON> Twitchell </PERSON> entered the plea at their arraignment Monday in <ORGANIZATION> Suffolk </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> on charges stemming from the April 8, 1986, death of their son <PERSON> Robyn </PERSON>. Magistrate <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON> set a pretrial conference for June 1, and ordered the Twitchells, who have two other sons, released on their recognizance. The Twitchells are the second Christian Science parents to be prosecuted in <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> and the first since 1971, when the state amended the child abuse and neglect law to recognize spiritual healing as an alternative to modern medicine. Followers of Christian Science refuse medicine or other health care on the belief that true understanding of God acts as a cure.
