 `` a possible collaborative program with -LRB- the company -RRB- in the context of the general agreement.'' But, he added, `` We do n't exclude the possibility that our cooperation will lead to a time where we might have a separate agreement'' with GA Technologies. Gas-cooled reactors have been widely used in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, but neither the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> nor the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> has favored them for civilian power. They do offer certain safety advantages, such as slow reaction to disturbances. Modular designs, which could be built efficiently in small sizes so utilities could add generating capacity only as needed, have attracted increasing attention both in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>, and the Soviets plan to complete construction of two in 1995. The modular high-temperature gas-cooled reactor is `` a good example of a safe, economically feasible new generation of reactor,'' <PERSON> Protsenko </PERSON> said.
