<HEAD>Trust Fund Suggested to Finance Future Flights</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By HARRY F. ROSENTHAL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> space committee proposed today that <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and industry explore setting up a trust fund to finance future American ventures in space. Such a fund, said Rep. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Roe </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.J. </LOCATION>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Science </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Space </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Technology </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, would work like the highway trust fund that financed the interstate highway system. <PERSON> Roe </PERSON> also said that the <ORGANIZATION> NASA </ORGANIZATION> budget authorization bill, which a subcommittee will take up Wednesday, will for the first time include a multiyear authorization. `` It stands to reason that any good and reasonable plan must have a duration of longer than a year,'' <PERSON> Roe </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aeronautics </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Astronautics </ORGANIZATION> at its annual meeting in nearby <LOCATION> Alexandria </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION> `` We insisted on the absurdity of funding our plans in one-year cycles.'' He said that had worked against rational planning because `` you can not devise a long-term research and development program, hold a tactical team together, and keep your facilities and equipment up to date if your primary concern is what next year's budget is going to be.'' <PERSON> Roe </PERSON> said the subcommittee will authorize spending for the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aeronautics </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Space </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> for fiscal 1