<BYLINE>By JILL LAWRENCE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> should pass a universal health insurance plan similar to the one signed into law last month by <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, former <ORGANIZATION> Cabinet </ORGANIZATION> member <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Califano </PERSON> said Tuesday. <PERSON> Califano </PERSON>, who was secretary of health, education and welfare during the <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> administration, said all other industrialized nations make health care or insurance available to their citizens. He said his son is working and studying at a West German hospital and receives full health coverage for $ 45 a month. `` We can do it in this country. The <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> plan provides a model,'' <PERSON> Califano </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> Joint </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Economic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>'s subcommittee on education and health at a hearing on the future of health care in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>. The plan advanced by <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, the likely Democratic presidential nominee, gives tax incentives to employers who offer health insurance to their employees and sets up a state fund to help the unemployed, the self-employed and others buy insurance for themselves at subsidized rates. The cost is estimated at $ 645 million over the next five years. Universal health insurance was one of three changes which <PERSON> Califano </PERSON> said he would make if he were trying to improve <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> health care and had no limits on what he could spend. He said he would also mount a huge health education and disease prevention campaign, and spend `` an enormous amount of money'' on research into addiction and the afflictions of the aged, particularly incontinence, immobility and memory loss. <PERSON> Califano </PERSON> said at least $ 1 billion a year should be spent on aging research and a new institut