inancing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>, said the trend toward higher spending on health care is inevitable and desirable. He said more and more money is becoming available for health care as national income increases. The aging of the population also contributes to higher expenditures, he said, as does the willingness of people to pay for more care, demonstrated by the rise in adult orthodontia.
