<HEAD>Crowe Says Iran A Serious Foe Despite Recent Setback</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDITOR'S NOTE _ The following was based on a Pentagon news pool
report.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ABOARD THE USS CORONADO IN THE PERSIAN GULF (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Joint </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chiefs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Staff </ORGANIZATION>, Adm. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Crowe </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, said Tuesday that <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> remains a dangerous foe in the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> despite heavy losses in battles with the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> two weeks ago. `` I believe the Iranians would clearly like to damage us, to hurt us, to humiliate us if they could,'' <PERSON> Crowe </PERSON>, the nation's top military commander, said during a surprise visit to the gulf. `` I think terrorism is one of the ways that they might try to do it. It's a very serious threat.'' <PERSON> Crowe </PERSON> presided at an awards ceremony on the sun-baked after deck of the 15,000-ton USS Coronado. He plans to visit at least three of the 28 other <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> warships in the area, including the mine-damaged 3,700-ton guided missile frigate <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Roberts </PERSON>, on his two-day tour. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> has warned <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> not to mount new military actions in the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> and has threatened reprisals from anywhere in the world. <PERSON> Crowe </PERSON> was interviewed by the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> media pool. The admiral said he was disappointed at the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration's decision against sending six fast <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> cutters to help patrol the gulf. `` They would have been very useful in these shallow waters because we need fast boats with shallow drafts,'' he said. `` They are the best patrol boats in the world and the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> had no substitute.'' <PERSON> Crowe </PERSON> said h