<HEAD>Contra Indians Surrender, Government Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An estimated 200 rebel Indians backed by the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> surrendered their weapons and agreed to join the <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION>, the government newspaper <ORGANIZATION> El </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nuevo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Diario </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday. It said the <ORGANIZATION> Indians </ORGANIZATION> agreed to stop military actions against the <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION> and to `` not allow the presence of guerrilla groups in the territory.'' The Indians, like other Contra groups operating from <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Costa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rica </LOCATION>, had <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> backing and fought the leftist Sandinista government since 1981. Tens of thousands of Miskito, <PERSON> Rama </PERSON> and Sumo Indians left their tribal homelands beginning in 1981 after the government tried to impose Marxism in the area and said it would move them to relocation camps. Many Indians crossed the <LOCATION> Rio </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coco </LOCATION> and sought refuge in <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> rather than move to relocation camps. Thousands took up arms, creating rebel movements which, like the larger Nicaraguan Resistance, received <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> aid. Most of the refugees have returned to their native 75-mile-long region along the <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> seaboard. The region is considered a national security area and foreigners are barred unless they have <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> permission. The Sandinistas some years ago acknowledged their errors with the Indians and sought their support. By March 1, nearly 7,000 had returned from Honduran refugee camps, according to the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> High Commissioner for Refugees. The government has not been as successful with other Contra groups. A fragile interim truce has been in pla