e </PERSON> also told the law enforcenment officials from 60 countries that crime in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> is climbing and that the spread and sale of drugs `` seems to be getting worse instead of better.'' Recalling his trip last month to <LOCATION> Latin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Meese </PERSON> said he flew over a coca field 75 miles wide and 200 miles long, proving the pervasive spread of cocaine production in the area. He said drug production now has `` a potential for undermining governments.'' Before the opening of the three-day meeting in <LOCATION> Rome </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Meese </PERSON> met with Justice Minister <PERSON> Giuliano </PERSON> <PERSON> Vassali </PERSON> to discuss improving extradition procedures between <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and to organize joint education programs for police and other law enforcement agencies. <PERSON> Meese </PERSON> said he granted an Italian request to consider transferring an Italian convicted of subversion, <PERSON> Silvia </PERSON> <PERSON> Baraldini </PERSON>, now in a high security prison in <LOCATION> Lexington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ky. </LOCATION>, to another facility currently under construction. Members of parliament have asked that her prison conditions be improved.
