<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A surge in imports caused <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s merchandise trade surplus to fall 7.2 percent to $ 94.3 billion in the 1987 fiscal year, the <ORGANIZATION> Finance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> has announced. Monday's report confirmed the continuing strength of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s economy in spite of the strong Japanese yen, which hurts the competitiveness of Japanese products in domestic and overseas markets Exports grew 10.5 percet to $ 233.4 billion, but imports grew even faster, rising 26.9 percent to $ 139.1 billion.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>'s second-largest bank says it is seeking to acquire a majority stake in <ORGANIZATION> Irving </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, but analysts say that swaying shareholders away from <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s competing hostile bid remains an uphill battle <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Italiana </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> SpA </ORGANIZATION>, which had sought a 45 percent stake in <LOCATION> Irving </LOCATION>, said Monday it would seek to purchase 9.5 million Irving shares, or about 51 percent of the New York-based bank, for $ 75 a share. <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> is offering $ 15 in cash and 1.575 shares of its stock for each of Irving's 18.5 million shares outstanding.
