<HEAD>Goodyear Workers Reject Contract</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Rubber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> is waiting for the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rubber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION> union to set the next course of action, now that a proposed three-year contract for 15,000 union employees at <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> plants in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> has been defeated, a <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> spokesman said today. `` Lacking a ratification, we agree with the union on working on a day-to-day basis,'' <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Perduyn </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> URW </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Curt </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said Monday night that the vote against the agreement by the union's largest branch, Local 12 in <LOCATION> Gadsden </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ala. </LOCATION>, was pivotal. The local, which has 2,900 members, voted 1,764 to 348 Monday against ratification. Six of the <ORGANIZATION> URW </ORGANIZATION>'s 11 <ORGANIZATION> Goodyear </ORGANIZATION> locals approved the proposed deal, but a majority of the membership of all 11 locals was opposed to it. Local 2 in <LOCATION> Akron </LOCATION> approved the agreement Sunday by a 3-to-1 ratio. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> did not reveal the final vote total among all 11 locals. The tentative agreement was reached in <LOCATION> Cincinnati </LOCATION> on April 21 at 2 a.m., two hours after the old contract had expired. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said he has heard that some locals were upset that the agreement did not contain a wage increase, although it included improved benefit and job security provisions. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> URW </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Milan </PERSON> <PERSON> Stone </PERSON> will contact the <ORGANI