<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Southdown </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Moore </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> McCormack </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Resources </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> say they will sell a <ORGANIZATION> Moore </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> McCormack </ORGANIZATION> energy subsidiary for about $ 148.7 million to <ORGANIZATION> CanadianOxy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Offshore </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Production </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co </ORGANIZATION>. The two resource companies said the proceeds from the sale of <ORGANIZATION> Moore </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> McCormack </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> will be used to help pay off loans made to <ORGANIZATION> Southdown </ORGANIZATION> for its recent $ 512 million acquisition of <ORGANIZATION> Moore </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> McCormack </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Resources </ORGANIZATION>. CanadianOxy Offshore Production is a subsidiary of <ORGANIZATION> Occidental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, a major oil company based in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>.
