<HEAD>Koppers Attorneys Accuse Shearson Of Using Inside Information</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> accused <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> on Tuesday of improperly trading <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> stock on the basis of inside information about the $ 1.7 billion hostile takeover attempt by <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> and British industrialist <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Beazer </PERSON>. A court document filed by <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> attorneys said <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> brokers accumulated <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> stock from January through early March for managed discretionary customer accounts. During the same period, which ended the day before the <ORGANIZATION> Beazer </ORGANIZATION> group announced a buyout offer, large amounts of <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> stock were sold for <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> discretionary accounts and for discretionary and managed discretionary accounts of <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s <PERSON> E.F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hutton </PERSON> unit. `` Based on information disclosed, <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s managed accounts performed as if they had a pipeline directly into the tender offer,'' the attorneys said in court documents filed in <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>. `` It is factually obvious that <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s preferential customers were enriched at the expense of all other discretionary accounts,'' the documents stated. The allegations were included in a motion filed in connection with <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION>' federal suit to block the <ORGANIZATION> Beazer </ORGANIZATION> group's takeover attempt. <ORGANIZATION> BNS </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> I